   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Harpaesis, foreman, to Matreas, the most honored, greetings. If it seems right to you, send me then for the costs of transport of the wheat, that is measured in the granaries, one hundred and sixty drachmas, total 160 drachmas, of which I shall render an account. The year 21 of Antoninus Caesar the Lord, the 12th Mesore. Give the 160 drachmas.</ab>
